<TD>
<IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/icons/icon1.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="ABSCENTER">
<FONT SIZE="1" color="#800080" face="Verdana, Arial">
posted 03-10-2001 12:50 AM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com/cgi-bin/ubb/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_profile&u=00000183" target=_blank>
<IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for taobob"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.monmouth.com/~robertl" target=_new><IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/homepage.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Author's Homepage"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com/cgi-bin/ubb/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=email&ToWhom=00000183" target=_blank><IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/email.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Email taobob"></A>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com/cgi-bin/ubb/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=private_message&u=00000183"><IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/priv_message.gif" BORDER='0' ALT="Send New Private Message"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com/cgi-bin/ubb/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=1&t=000171&reply_num=000000&u="><IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com/cgi-bin/ubb/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=1&t=000171&replyto=000000"><IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I STILL do not see the need for an INDIVIDUAL mini-game like this. I realize that this was not created in a way that would occupy development resources, but this game should have been a give away for players of Everquest and not something that should be conducted in game because it is too distracting from the "environment". I would have rather seen this given away to players as freeware, rather than an in game activity.<BR>There are too many things about this that do not fit in with the "vision" Verant is constantly preaching that I can't even comprehend it... <P>1. Verant wants to discourage soloing, and gives players an experience bonus for grouping, and then creates an individual based mini game for "downtime"... This could not only interfere with groups, but also sort of encourages/rewards soloing and then sitting recovering rather than efficient group killing....<P>I am sure that this will continue to happen (and HAS already): "I was playing gems, and I didn't see that your health had gone down so fast". Players have already begun dying, then complaining, petitioning the GMs, and getting upset because of deaths.. Doesn't anyone else see this blowing up in Verant's face and that it can only get worse... <P>In a balanced group there is rarely downtime that is significant, and I have been in plenty of groups where people meditate through pulls.... I just see this as an unnecessary addition, that will be more trouble than it is worth in the long run (at least from my perspective). The chat interface is designed to give you something to keep you occupied in "downtime" and that is to communicate with the players around you AS your character.<P>Absor has already responded that he personally doesn't want there to be a tag notifying people that someone is playing gems, and is also opposed to giving group leaders the ability to disable this (which was my suggestion). This has already happened where groups have died and lost experience due to "I wasn't paying attention to your health, I was playing gems" players, and this can be avoided by adding these. Characters want to assure that people they are grouped "covering their backs", and although people DO go afk, watch TV, vacuum etc. when playing, these are the same people who get groups killed currently.<P>I do not see the GEMS feature actually breeding harmony between players, and THE ANGRY FEW would take death at the hands of Tetris addicts reason for a direct confrontation. With the added stress of a corpse run this could breed bad blood between players (especially those who are stuggling compared to those who are say "well equipped", carefree, or fall into the bad player realm already)...<P>Seriously from a role playing standpoint I want the person meditating to be trying to stay in tune with the environment by paying attention to the chat (and focusing his energy from the environment) rather than playing Tetris (or reading a book, vacuuming, or whatever)... While meditating, there are plenty of things to do, including using emotes to make your character come to life. Another reason that it bothers me is that from a Role-play standpoint we will see zone-wide arguments about deaths by this, as well as spam about scores and COMPETITION (like EQ doesn't already have enough of that).... <P>Even if I were to disable shout (which is useful for knowing about trains and communicating to the entire zone) as well as /ooc I would still be subjected to gems discussions. People everywhere are talking about it, so even were I to remove these channels someone would still mention it. I also needed to remove myself from a so called RP guild because they were discussing gems.. Of course saying something about not wanting to hear about gems would result in more arguments, and even though I don't want to hear about it at all, I don't want to start arguments either.<P>It's not only about people doing this in group, my problem with it is that GOOD groups are hard enough to find (and soloers will love this game).... I simply don't want this to start impacting in &lt;more&gt; group deaths, not to mention the chattering about high scores that will fill zones as well as groups.<P>I just don't think giving this feature in game is something that was going to help immersiveness, and not only that but it will impact me... They want us to group, and this will hurt the group mechanic, This comment by DCM_Skidmark says it all:<BR>"Gems was made for those who solo or when your in the city selling items you got from Guk. or when your camping the AC need i say more. leave it to some players to complain. When verant tries to give us something to do to pass the time. During downtime. As always though there are people who are gonna sit in lower guk and play gems cause they are addicted. OPPS sorry i didnt heal the tank in time i am on wave 20. Disband and ignore." <P>2. Verant wants to enforce naming rules to preserve the "immersiveness", they then add a puzzle game to ruin it and then give players something to spam throughout chat &lt;high scores and competition&gt; and remove them from the environment as well.<P>GEMS is even worse of a detraction than bad names and reduces EQ to the level of a chat room, meaning that Verant has abandoned their "vision"... Not only will they need to hire more GMs when people start complaining about GEMs spam and deaths, but they will also be making competition and in some cases disputes between players worse....<P>I think that Verant has finally destroyed the EQ environment completely (with GEMS), even in the light of the naming policy enforcement that they were trying to use to retain their integrity of the "World"... The world of Norrath I envisioned was for "playing your role" (ie RP) and I personally didn't want any reminder of the outside world, and the names (and rampant twinking) were a major detraction from that.<P>Currently, the majority of players do not adhere to their roles (i.e. stay in character), don't name themselves to suit the fantasy environment, or play the game as Verant once intended (RPG anyone?). Now, they have a way to further remove them from the environment (whether it's as a distraction or as a high scoring competition). <P>Another comment to refute, this one by Leolo:<BR>"As for roleplaying, with the few hundred thousand people playing EQ your chances of complete roleplaying are slim already, besides that point, adding a game that you can play isn't against roleplaying at all. If your character is going to sit for 10 , do you actually think s/he would just sit there looking at the same thing...no, they would probably pass their time with some sort of game, be it cards, possibly a variant of gems, etc"<P>If the character has downtime, then there are ALREADY plenty of things that they can do to occupy themselves, most of which are beneficial to actually work on. Players can work on their trade skills during self imposed downtime, or conversate with each other, and I find that more conducive to role-playing than Gems ever will be… People who want to play a "personally suited" game during downtime would be better served by playing another game that did not rely on a multi-player dynamic. <P>This game was Verant's (temporary) solution to complaints about "downtime", that amazingly didn't require any of their resources, and rather than actually fix those problems they distract from it. Players make downtime themselves, mostly by soloing or camping, or sitting around trying to sell something... I personally see no reason why there should be a mini-game for "downtime" that is player created, especially one that is individual and not multi-player.<P>3. Verant wants to stop camping, and kill stealing as well as preserve community. Then Verant gives these same "downtime", camping something people a game to play to keep them VERY occupied while waiting for Uberitemguy_00 to spawn, followed by people stealing kills from them...<P>For those of you saying that GEMs is the perfect thing to alleviate "downtime" when waiting for things to spawn, well then what happens when someone comes in and steals the spawn?? <P>I already think that "sitting" a spawn is an incredible waste of time, that breeds arguments, removes exp from people who should be earning it and destroys the economy, and Verant (who has been opposed to this) is now encouraging it. For a group camping experience this is obviously different, but Verant adding to the competition and arguments is what I don't understand.<P><BR>The main reason that I disagree with Verant's inclusion of this is that I began playing EQ because it WAS a role-playing game, and it is hardly that anymore with all the "d00ds", power-gamers, twinks, ill-naming and immaturity.. Since Everquest became a mainstream product there is little or no role-playing left, and this IS NOT the way to encourage that. <P>Many times role-players have asked that Verant do something to keep the integrity of the role-play atmosphere, but they have been refused at every turn... (whether it be the simple enforcement of the naming policy or the inclusion of a "role-play server" where people can only have one character and role-playing is encouraged) Verant adding Gems to the game has finally admitted that they don't encourage role-playing, and that instead they cater to the other crowd of mainstream, chat room, hack and slash teenagers and not the age 20 to 30 something, Role-players who gave this game it's start.. <P>Maybe Verant just admitted "It's broke and we can't fix it" and decided that they didn't care anymore and they want it to end. They want everyone to leave even the ones the game was designed for, who might have actually stayed. I as a role-player would've probably stayed when the mass migration happened (ahem new games), but this was seriously not implemented with the intention of retaining the "immersiveness" or the role-playing environment of Everquest....<P>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
