<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
dude... lighten up. according to absor, gems was created by a programmer who was home sick. i seriously doubt that it was placed in the game to solve the so called 'problem' of downtime, but i am quite certain that it was just for fun. <P>what's fun, you ask? well, its when people relax the veins straining out of their foreheads, and celebrate the advantages of something, instead of posting riduclously long essays on internet forums.<P>and as far as roleplaying and everquest... i know many EQers who roleplay in RL(incl me), and for the most part, they do not treat EQ as a roleplaying game, but as a computer game. the simple fact is that you are never going to get a fully immersive, roleplaying environment going while under the constrictions of a programmed game, because even if the game has been years in development, it will never have the adaptability and creativity of a GM's mind. as soon as roleplaying is codified and slapped on a computer, you lose the infinite possibilities that exist within the human mind.<P>and if you are such a hardcore roleplayer, how do you deal with the concept of zones? in a proper roleplaying game characters shouldn't be left in suspended animation for 30 seconds every time they go to a new area....<P><BR>lighten up.. enjoy eq for what it is, not whine about what it is not.
</FONT>
