Well Taobob, why are you trying to put me down because i am currently a soloer!?<BR>First of all, it IS a game, and it is not made for grouping only, yes it is a multi-user game, i think that after playing it for a full year i would know that, but it is also made for soloing fyi, even while soloing one can enjoy the benefits of it being multi-user, while traveling or exploring or the occasional grouping, or to suddenly decide to help out newbies for fun, one can still interact with other ppl eventhough they are not consistently grouping when hunting for xp...  So what if i hunt alone but still take advantage of the other benefits of EQ being a multi-user game?  you have a problem with that???  There is indeed a small portion of the game for casual players like i am atm, and we ARE allowed to play alone too you know, if not, why don't Verant just take the soloing ability of the Necro and druids out??  <BR>And you know what, I know the mechanics of grouping very well indeed so don't come bashing my grouping abilities because you have no idea who i am and how many characters i have in the game, i lvld a SK to 36 when the xp penalty was still there, and if you played one then you know soloing was not an viable option for a SK over lvl 20.  I started many other characters, but none made it past 20 cuz i did not like their classes, i liked my Sk too much and now my Necro, which just turned 39(yeay, new spells!).  I started a Necro simply because grouping had become too hard for my SK, i started working on several things in RL and could only play an hour or two at a time and by the time you find an appropriate group you usually have to look for a replacement already cuz you have to camp, plus xp gain was sooo slow, and many many groups would not even want an SK most of the time cuz of the xp penalty to the group which only made it worse to find a group, which is not good when you have only 2 hours to play...  I know the xp situation has improved recently though, and have started playing my SK again...  but now i like my necro more than my SK am afraid so he will lvl faster...  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR>N e way, don't you come tell me about the benefits of grouping and soloing, i think i know them pretty well, i am not saying i know the game more than you, but i am not a newbie either.<BR>As for sitting on my lazy bastard ass for camping stuff, as you say, you could not be more wrong and your head is pretty far up your own ass for saying such a thing without knowing who i am in the game, you are making me think you are not that much of a big time EQ player cuz you would know that if you are out questing for one of your class's item, you will have to camp some mobs for quite a loooong time sometimes, i have quested most of my stuff, mostly cuz i believe in the fun of questing one's own class specific stuff, eventhough it is pretty long to do at times, like for my Harvester, Shadowbound gloves/boots and robe of Enshroudment, and now trying the AC, so you are saying i was just sitting on my lazy ass camping these mobs that i needed???  I would call questing for my own stuff exploring and adventure, don't you??  That is more questing than what most ppl do on an old server like the one i am on where ppl would rather buy the stuff rather than questing it.  What about when i wanted a runed circlet for myself and instead of buying one i went to Perma to camp the preacher to get one for myself, which took me 6 hours for one circlet plus 4 morning stars, that was also not appropriate with the rules of the game???  I was suppose to drag a group all the way to Perma for a 6 hour camp for my circlet when i could do it alone by the time i reached 30, or in the middle of OOT for the gobo headmaster, which took me 3 different days at 3 hours a day to get??  With a 20 min spawn time, if gems had been on at the time i would have played it instead of reading a book waiting for my quest pieces...  I was just being a lazy nonexplorator not following the rules because i wanted to camp for my own stuff, hey???  I think you have the rules wrong buddy, the game is for everyone, it is indeed made towards grouping but it is not for that only purpose at ALL times, because one also solos I don't thing that is against the rules.  When i do want a group i look for one or play my SK, don't blame Verant or GEMS for affecting your group because someone was playing gems, it is that person's own fault for not looking after their responsability and for playing gems when it was not appropriate.  It is people behind the characters and the machines you know.  <BR>I understand what you are saying that gems doesn't really have a fantasy role, but don't bash ppl because they like it, i think it is a great attempt done by Verant to give something to do ingame during downtime for ppl like me, when appropriately used.  With a population of 360,000 users, i am sure there are other casual players like me who solo when they are on for only an hour, and then group or explore when they can finally get an afternoon or a night to play...  You hate gems that much?  then don't play it.  If someone is negatively affecting the group cuz they are playing gems, then kick him out of the group!  One can do many other things to negatively affect a group, gems is now just one of these options...  Like the other one said, should you petition to get someone's TV taken away because they were watching a movie on a Sony TV and were not paying attention to their group and someone died?...<P>Nebuk<BR>39th season leading his dead minions<BR>May the Prince bless you with Death<BR>&lt;I play on Innoruuk server for anyone interested to give a tell or to meet&gt;
