Taobob I think im right in saying that your point was that Verant is saying one thing and doing another. Two of your main contentions being that GEMS is only a help to those higher lvl characters who want to camp a spawn for that rare drop item, and that it caters to those soloers out there. But have you not seen what they have done on Odus and specifically the Warrens, they are testing a new way to hinder this. If you or your group as a whole are to high lvl for a particular creature you are not going to get any lore items or no drop items. Also that dungeon was created so that newbies could have an oppurtunity to learn more about group dynamics at an earlier lvl and hopefully get them to group in the later lvls. It seems to me that at least in some way Verant is supporting their claim that they want to make the game more group based and stop those higher lvls from camping spawns. Sure you may find GEMS offensive but i find it EXTREMELY offensive that EQ is now filled with a bunch of people who love to whine about the current changes Verant is making. Those guys are working their arshes off trying to make this game more enjoyable for everyone, because ultimately thats what its all about FUN pure and simple. Now you can say what ever you want about soloing and how those that do it are anti social but its simply not true my friend plays EQ and he just doesnt like to group he says "there are alot of really stupid people on EQ." He still interacts with others online just not in a group. Personally i like to group but dont harp on someone because they prefer to solo remember its all about one thing and thats fun. if someone has more fun soloing let them do it, if someone likes to play GEMS in their downtime let them do it. The game was made and is being changed with the interest of everyone in mind not only for you or anyone else who agrees with you.  
