How do I use gems? It sounds like something that would make me want to keep playing the game more.<P>Supremacists like Taobob really get on my threpenny bits "You MUST not play the game like this, you MUST only play it the way I want to play it".  That attitude just bites.<P>We don't all have 25-30 hours a week to dedicate to playing a game. My usual log in is about one and a half to two hours, maybe twice a week.  If I play my cards right my wife will let me group for a few hours at the weekend, but who wants to group for an hour? And I feel guilty if I accept an invite knowing I will be logging soon.<P>Taobob, what you need is your own server where you and all the like minded 50+ roleplaying fanatics can hang out together and leave the rest of us to just enjoy the game the best we can.<P>I mean if roleplaying is so central to the game what's the point of a character race like Dark Elves? Who'd group with them apart from more Dark Elves?<P>Gems sounds like a decent way to pass the time while resting / medding - at least you're looking at the screen and likely to see group messages (messages you tend to miss if you've gone downstairs to the kitchen for a beer / cup of tea 8)).
