<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
To start off I would like to say that it is impossible to suggest that everyone on EQ roleplay or play the game the same way you do.  This game supports too wide of an age group to even suggest such a thing. Now before I get some idiot trying to reem me about the user policty of 18+, let me say that I have personally grouped with a father and son combo, where the son couldn't hardly type a sentence yet he had his own account because "Dad" is an EQ junky and said it was ok.  To these guys EQ time was quality time with each other and they enjoyed it.  For a moment put yourself in Dad's shoes and tell your 8 year old son "No you can't play with me on this game because you don't know how to roleplay!"  Screw that this game is meant to be entertaining, that means FUN, you know something to do to pass time until you have to get back to the real world of work and school or housework.  If you're getting all bent out of shape because the game isn't what you want it to be then in my opionion it's time to find yourself another game regardless of how long you've been here yadda yadda.  If you want to roleplay then by all means do so, when I personally meet someone that is trying to roleplay I attempt to humor them the best that I can, but I am one person on a server of 100's and can't expect everyone to do the same.  Last I would like to point out that this is just a game, granted we all hate dying and losing exp and whatever but it's part of the game that's why you never see a "Game Over" message on EQ because they know people are going to die. If I ever get to a point that I can't die in this game and laugh about it then it's time to click &lt;cancel&gt; on my subscribtion because I've become way too crotchety in my old age to be bothered with something like EQ and need to settle down with something a little less nerve wracking like say Checkers?  It's outrageous to think that everyone has the ability to sit down in front of their pc and completely zone out the things that are happening in real life, people are going to watch TV, they are going to take bathroom breaks, they are going to make runs to the fridge to grab stuff, and you are still going to walk through a zone and see a few players &lt;AFK&gt; while they change a dirty diaper or refill a Sippy Cup or take the dog out for a whizz so what's the deal with one more little interruption?  Whether I die from someone playing Gems or because the group cleric was attending to a R/L problem, I really don't care, get up, get your stuff and get back in the game.  Draw steel and slay the (/ooc brb baby cryin) beast! Heh heh there's yer roleplay.
</FONT>
